Meta Horizon Privacy Guide for Children
18 likes
Updated:
a week ago
As of 31 March 2025, Move will be discontinued and no longer available in Meta Horizon OS and the Meta Horizon mobile app.
Your privacy on Meta Horizon
This privacy guide is for children between 10 and 12 years old (these ages may differ by region). If you're a teen, an adult or a parent/guardian, take a look at our
Supplemental Meta Platforms Technologies Privacy Policy
and
Parental Privacy Disclosure
to learn more.
We've written this privacy guide to help you understand what types of personal information Meta collects and how it is used to give you the best experience in mixed reality (MR).
If you need help with understanding anything in this privacy guide, please talk to your parent, guardian or the adult who looks after you.
How do I set up my Meta account and how does it work?
Your parent or guardian must create and manage your Meta account for you. They have this ability so that they can help you have a safer and age-appropriate experience in MR. Your parent can:
See, change or download information, such as your name, date of birth, email address or account password, and delete your Meta account.
Approve your app downloads and purchases, buy tokens for you to purchase digital goods and manage which Horizon worlds you can access, create and collaborate on.
See how much time you are spending in MR and choose how long and when you can use your device and apps.
See who you are following and being followed by, block people and see anyone that you have reported to Meta. They can also choose to approve your follower and following requests.
Add people as "approved contacts" that you can call and chat with (but you can remove these contacts at any time). These users will also be able to send or receive travel invitations from you to join you in an app or experience.
See and change your activity settings, such as showing others whether you are online or not, what apps you are using in MR and which Horizon world you are in.
When you've turned 13 (or 14, depending on where you live), you'll start managing your account by yourself. Learn more about what this means
here
. We'll send you more information before then so that you know what to do.
What information does Meta have about me and where do they get this from?
Information that you and your parent/guardian give us
. This includes the information given when you set up an account, such as your name, date of birth, username and password. Your parent/guardian can also choose to give us more information about you, such as the apps that you use or settings that you choose, to help improve your overall experience in MR.
Location information that we collect from your device
. This helps us to understand your general location, but we do not know information such as your address.
Information as you use your device.
Physical movements.
For example, the position of your headset or body movements. If your parent/guardian allows you to use the hand and body tracking feature, we also know information such as your estimated hand size and hand and body pose.
Fitness information.
If your parent/guardian allows you to use Meta Quest Move, we will also know information about your fitness activities.
Your activity in Meta Quest devices and apps
. For example, the apps you download, the time, frequency and duration of your activities, and your actions in a game.
Environmental information and dimensions.
For example, information about your surroundings such as the size of walls, surfaces and objects in your room and the distances between them and your headset for experiences that blend your virtual and real-world environments.
Learn more
.
Video and audio information
. We get this information when your cameras and microphones are turned on.
Your content
. Such as the objects that you build and information, such as the date and time that you created the content.
Recordings
. Additionally, when you use Horizon Worlds, the last few minutes of your most recent audio, video and other interactions are recorded in case you want to report anything. Other users may also submit recordings of the same event. We do not review these recordings unless you submit a report and the recordings are deleted on a rolling basis. These recordings are for your safety.
Information about you and other users.
Such as who you follow, your approved contacts and if you are managed or supervised by the same parent/guardian as another user.
Information that others give us.
For example, app developers may tell us if they know that you are under or over 13. They might also tell us about your achievements and what features you use in the apps. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of these other companies with your parent/guardian to learn how they handle any information that you choose to share if you use their apps.
How and why does Meta use my information?
We use your information for things such as:
Providing and improving our services.
Promoting safety and security
. This helps us to give you an age-appropriate experience in MR. Additionally, if you submit a report, we use recordings to investigate and resolve the report, and to help train our systems to better combat harmful behaviour.
Showing you things that we think you might like
. We use information, such as your age, chosen language, general location and people that you are connected with to provide you with additional product functionalities and safe and age-appropriate experiences, so that you can invite people and be placed in apps and worlds with people that you know, people your parent/guardian have approved and/or others your age for gameplay. Your parent/guardian can choose to give us more information, such as the apps that you download and use or the Horizon worlds that your approved contacts have visited, to further personalise your experiences in MR and help you find more age-appropriate and relevant experiences. Your followers, approved contacts and people that you follow might also appear higher in your search results.
Communicating with you
. For example, we may send you information to let you know about changes to your account.
Will anyone else see my information?
We share some of your information:
With your parent/guardian.
With other users. Your Meta Horizon profile information (such as your display name, username, profile picture and avatar) can always be seen by others. When your parent/guardian allows you to download and use a multi-player app, other users can also see your activity and your Meta Horizon profile information and can send you follow requests.
Your followers will be able to see your activity, such as the apps that you use and your achievements.
Other people who are managed or supervised by the same parent/guardian will be able to see the fact you have a parent-managed account and the apps you have.
With other companies that we work with, such as app developers, but only if your parent/guardian has given you access to their app and they need the information to provide it.
When we need to for legal reasons.
What are my rights?
You can ask us at any time if you want to see, change, delete or stop us from using your information. You can also tell us if you are concerned about anything that we are doing with your information or if you want to make a complaint.
If you need any help with these things, you can always chat to your parent/guardian and you can find more information on our
Privacy Centre
.
Where can I find out more information?
For more details, please ask your parent/guardian to help you read our
Supplemental Meta Platforms Technologies Privacy Policy
and
Parental Privacy Disclosure
. You can also take a look at our Help Centre to learn more about your privacy and Meta account.
